HTML iframe is used to display a web page within a web page.
<body>
<h2>HTML Iframes</h2>
<p>You can also use the CSS height and width properties to specify the size of the iframe:</p>
<iframe src="demo_iframe.htm" style="height:100px;width:300px" title="Iframe Example"></iframe>
</body>

we can set target of iframe in <a>
<body>
<iframe src="demo_iframe.htm" name="iframe_a" height="300px" width="100%" title="Iframe Example"></iframe>
<p><a href="https://www.w3schools.com" target="iframe_a">W3Schools.com</a></p>
<p>When the target attribute of a link matches the name of an iframe, the link will open in the iframe.</p>
</body>
