----------------------------------------------------------------------------
actual height = height + padding + border
actual width  = width + padding + border
With box-sizing, padding and border are included in mentioned height & width only
.div2 {
  width: 300px;
  height: 100px;
  padding: 50px;
  border: 1px solid red;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
clear property specifies what should happen with the element that is next to a floating element.
both	The element is pushed below both left and right floated elements
article {
  float: left;
  padding: 20px;
  width: 70%;
  background-color: #f1f1f1;
  height: 300px; /* only for demonstration, should be removed */
}

/* Clear floats after the columns */
section::after {
  content: "";    -> to add some content before or after the section 
  display: table; -> let the element behave like table element
  clear: both;    -> both The element is pushed below both left and right floated elements
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
responsive
1. As per device, page will increase size
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
2. use max-width property is set to 100% or width: 100%
<img src="img_girl.jpg" style="width:100%;">
<img src="img_girl.jpg" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;">
3. provide multiple images
<picture>
  <source srcset="img_smallflower.jpg" media="(max-width: 600px)">
  <source srcset="img_flowers.jpg" media="(max-width: 1500px)">
  <source srcset="flowers.jpg">
  <img src="img_smallflower.jpg" alt="Flowers">
</picture>
4. use font-size vw unit
<h1 style="font-size:10vw">Hello World</h1>
5. use media queries
/* Use a media query to add a break point at 800px: */
@media screen and (max-width: 800px) {
  .left, .main, .right {
    width: 100%; /* The width is 100%, when the viewport is 800px or smaller */
  }
}
6. usee css3 or bootstrap
